{"type":"message-part","messageId":"a99f52e8-fe47-4a45-af00-409542a1e8ef","role":"user","index":0,"part":{"type":"text","text":"# Preserving your work\n\nSave a copy of files you create during this task to `/logs/artifacts/`. This directory is preserved after the run so outputs can be inspected. Organize with subdirectories if helpful (e.g., `/logs/artifacts/code/`, `/logs/artifacts/reports/`). The directory already exists and is writable.\n\n---\n\n# Python Windmill Script with Optional Parameters\n\n## Background\n\nWindmill Python scripts support optional parameters with default values, just like TypeScript scripts. When a parameter has a default, it becomes optional in Windmill's auto-generated UI form. This is useful for building configurable scripts that work out-of-the-box with sensible defaults.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Create a Python script at `/home/user/windmill-project/f/scripts/send_notification.py`.\n- The `main` function must have this signature:\n  ```python\n  def main(\n      message: str,\n      recipient: str = \"admin@example.com\",\n      subject: str = \"Notification\",\n      priority: int = 1\n  ) -> dict:\n  ```\n- The function must return a dict:\n  ```python\n  {\n      \"to\": recipient,\n      \"subject\": subject,\n      \"body\": message,\n      \"priority\": priority,\n      \"sent\": False   # simulated — no real email is sent\n  }\n  ```\n- Create the metadata file at `/home/user/windmill-project/f/scripts/send_notification.script.yaml` with:\n  - `summary: \"Prepare a notification payload\"`\n  - `language: python3`\n\n## Implementation Guide\n\n1. Create `f/scripts/send_notification.py` with the function above.\n2. Create `f/scripts/send_notification.script.yaml`.\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Project path: `/home/user/windmill-project`\n- `sent` must always be `False` (simulation only — no real sending)\n- Return dict keys must be exactly: `to`, `subject`, `body`, `priority`, `sent`\n\n## Integrations\n\nNone."}}
